# Soli Deo Gloria — A Public Domain Dedication

*All glory to God.*

Johann Sebastian Bach inscribed these words on his manuscripts to
declare that his work belonged not to himself but to something greater.
Leo Tolstoy held the same conviction. In the final decades of his life
he renounced copyright on his writings, insisting that ideas and art
should flow freely to all who need them.

This project follows in that tradition. The original work across all
repositories in the tolstoy.life organisation — wiki content, editorial
prose, markup, metadata, design, and code created by its contributors —
is dedicated to the worldwide public domain.

## Dedication

To the extent possible under law, the contributors to this project
waive all copyright and related or neighbouring rights to their
original contributions. This dedication applies worldwide and is
intended to be irrevocable. Anyone is free to copy, modify, publish,
use, compile, sell, or distribute this work, in any form and for any
purpose, commercial or non-commercial, without asking permission.

Where the law does not recognise a waiver of copyright, the
contributors grant every person an unconditional, perpetual,
irrevocable, royalty-free licence to exercise all rights under
copyright in their contributions, for any purpose whatsoever and
without any conditions.

## Source texts

The literary works of Leo Tolstoy reproduced in this project were
first published in the 19th and early 20th centuries and are in the
public domain worldwide. The contributors make no claim of copyright
over these source texts.

## Third-party sources and dependencies

This project draws on data and tools from third parties. Their licences
apply to their respective materials and are not altered by this
dedication.

**tolstoydigital TEI/XML** — person, location, and work reference data
extracted from the [tolstoydigital](https://tolstoydigital.org/) TEI
corpus is licensed under **CC BY-SA**. Attribution is required, and
derivative works incorporating this data must carry the same licence.
Wiki pages that draw on tolstoydigital data cite the source per the
project's sourcing rules.

**Standard Ebooks tools** — the ebook production toolchain in `tools/`
is a fork of [Standard Ebooks](https://standardebooks.org/) and is
released under **GPLv3**, with the exception of ebook templates in
`se/data/templates/` which are **CC0** (public domain). See
`tools/LICENSE.md` for details.

**Eleventy Excellent** — the website frontend is built on the Eleventy
Excellent starter (**ISC licence**, Lene Saile) which uses Cube
Boilerplate (**MIT licence**, Set Studio). See `website/LICENSE` for
the full text of these licences.

